    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I've also heard some legal scholars argue that focusing so much on \"historical tradition\" can be a problem because it might prevent the law from evolving to protect new rights that weren't recognized in the past. Do you think that's a valid criticism of how substantive due process is used?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
