      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That criticism is a sophisticated and persistent academic critique, often voiced by those who favor a more strictly textualist or originalist view of the Constitution. The argument is that an overly rigid reliance on historical precedent can indeed stifle necessary social progress and fail to protect rights relevant to modern life. However, the counterargument is that without anchoring rights in established tradition, the concept becomes dangerously subjective and vulnerable to the whims of the current political majority.",
      "source": "target",
